code_values.text: Inap.: U.S. territory or foreign country

ER82007.label: FAMILY COMPOSITION CHANGE
ER82007.description: Family Composition Change between the 2021 and 2023 Waves. All recontact cases, including splitoffs from recontacts, are coded 8 for this variable. Codes 2-8 have priority over codes 0 and 1 and code 8 has priority over everything else.

code_values.text: No change; no movers-in or movers-out of the family
Change in members other than Reference Person or Spouse/Partner only
Reference Person is the same person as in 2021 but Spouse/Partner left or died; Reference Person has new Spouse/Partner; used also when cohabiting, nonrelative female becomes Partner
Spouse/Partner from 2021 is now Reference Person
2021 female Reference Person got married--spouse (usually a nonsample member) is now Reference Person. Used also when cohabiting nonrelative male becomes Reference Person
Some sample individual other than 2021 Reference Person or Spouse/Partner has become Reference Person of this FU. (Used primarily for male and unmarried female splitoffs.)
Some sample female other than 2021 Reference Person got married and their spouse is now Reference Person. (Used primarily for married female splitoffs.)
Female Reference Person in 2021 with spouse in institution-- spouse in FU in 2023 and is now Reference Person

Other (used for recontacts and recombined families--these latter are usually Reference Persons and spouses/partners who have parted for a wave or more, been interviewed separately, and who have reconciled at some time since the 2021 interview but prior to the 2023 interview).

Neither Reference Person nor Spouse/Partner (if there is one) is a sample member and neither of them was a Reference Person or Spouse/Partner last year. (Used primarily for underage splitoff children.)

ER82008.label: TYPE INSTITUTION
ER82008.description: Type of Institution for Entire FU

code_values.text: Educational facility--dormitory, other on-campus housing, etc.

ER82009.label: 1968 FAMILY IDENTIFIER
ER82009.description: This variable is the 1968 family ID number. Individuals associated with families from the Immigrant sample, added to the PSID in 1997 and 1999, were assigned 1968 IDs so that they, too, have unique identifiers compatible with the PSID structure for the Core (SRC and Census) sample.

code_values.text: Family from the 1968 SRC cross-section sample
Family from the Immigrant sample added in 1997 and 1999. Values of 3001-3441 indicate families first interviewed in 1997; values of 3442-3511 indicate families not interviewed until 1999.
Family from the Immigrant sample added in 2017 and 2021. Values of 4001-4462 indicate families first interviewed in 2017; values of 4700-4851 indicate families not interviewed until 2021.

ER82010.label: WTR REINSTATED DROPPED FAMILY
ER82010.description: Whether This FU Is Related to the SEO/Census Sample Cut

code_values.text: Yes, this FU is from a 1968 family that was dropped
No, this FU is from a 1968 family that was kept

ER82011.label: INTERVIEWER ID
ER82011.description: The values in this variable represent the 7-digit identification number assigned to each interviewer by the Survey Research Center's Survey Operations Office as his or her personal identifier. Users should note, that all cases (including those which are self-administered and completed in a web mode) are assigned to an interviewer initially.

code_values.text: Interviewer is unknown; case was assigned to centralized staff

ER82014.label: YEAR CURRENT IW
ER82014.description: Year of Current Interview. A handful of case were finalized and delivered in 2024 rather than 2023.

ER82015.label: DATA QUALITY FLAG
ER82015.description: Due to some technical issues with the the data collection software, some cases were identified as having skip logic issues. We have carefully reviewed and fixed these cases during data processing; however, it is possible some anomolies may remain.

code_values.text: Case Identified as having possibly data quality issues

ER82016.label: LENGTH OF IW IN MINUTES
ER82016.description: Elapsed interview length in minutes excluding the coverscreen, payment, and address collection sections.

ER82017.label: # IN FU
ER82017.description: This variable represents the actual number of persons currently in the FU.

ER82018.label: AGE OF REFERENCE PERSON
ER82018.description: This variable represents the actual age of the 2023 Reference Person of the FU. The minimum value is usually 18, although in rare cases a person under 18 might become Reference Person.

ER82020.label: AGE OF SPOUSE
ER82020.description: This variable represents the actual age of the current Spouse or Partner (cohabiting friend). Spouses/Partners aged 14-16 are rare.

code_values.text: Inap.: Reference Person is female or single male; no Spouse/Partner in FU (ER83493=5)
Inap.: Reference Person is single male or female; no Spouse/Partner in FU (ER83493=5)

ER82022.label: # CHILDREN IN FU
ER82022.description: This variable represents the actual number of persons currently in the FU who are neither Reference Person nor Spouse/Partner, from newborns through those 17 years of age, whether or not they are actually children of the Reference Person or Spouse/Partner.

ER82023.label: AGE YOUNGEST CHILD
ER82023.description: The range of values for this variable represents the actual age in years of the youngest FU Member in this age range and excludes Reference Persons and Spouses/Partners; note that a child's age is not coded 02 (two years old) until he/she reaches his/her second birthday.

code_values.text: Inap.: no persons aged 17 or younger in FU

ER82024.label: # NONFU SHARING HU

ER85429.label: # OF INDIVIDUAL RECORDS
ER85429.description: Total Number of Individual Data Records Associated with 2023 Family Unit. The values for this variable represent the number of individual-level data records on the Cross-Year Individual File having the same family-level data in 2023, that is, all persons in the family in 2023 and any institutionalized individuals associated with the family, as well as any movers-out between 2019 and 2023 who are not included in another responding family.

ER85768.label: TOTAL EXPENDITURE

Total Consumption with Rental Value, includes the following expenses: food at home, food delivered, food eaten out, hospital, doctor bills, prescriptions, health insurance, rent value, rent, utilities, telephone & internet, homeowners insurance, household repairs, household furnishings, vehicle loans, vehicle leases, vehicle down payments, auto insurance, additional vehicle expenses, vehicle repairs, gasoline, parking, bus, taxi, other transportation expenses, education, childcare, clothing, trips, other recreation, and computing expenses. ER82882.description: FOOD1. Now I'm going to read you several statements that people have made about their food situation.
